cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.SY

The paper discusses a system that utilizes speech disturbance and delayed auditory feedback to disrupt human speech. This falls under the categories of speech processing (cs.SD), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and natural language processing (cs.CL). The system also has potential applications in facilitating and controlling discussions, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the need for future formal studies, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
